First thing you want to do is get yourself a good quantity of cash, around 2500pp should do it (which these days it seems is pennies /sigh) then you want to head to your nearest Alchemist.<br>
Buy as MUCH Mandrake root as your little body can possibly hold and find yourself a nice comfortable spot to sit for the next hour =)<br>
<br>
Combine 2 Mandrake Roots (not stacked of course) in a sewing kit (Large or Small) to make Mandrake Weave (stackable).  You want to save these Mandrake Weaves.  <br>
<br>
Mandrake Root cost between 2-3pp each for Dubious faction in SH..could be less in other places so find your best place because you will be buying a lot of them and those few gold you save will help a lot.<br>
<br>
This combination is trivial at 66 which is high enough already for what we need to do..but you remember all those Mandrake Weaves we had? Well guess what? You need to have Smithing skill for ring quest too so make Boning! Combine One Brick of ore, flask of water, and a file in a Forge to do this..this is trivial at 37.  Now combine this boning with our Mandrake Weave to make 10 yes Ten Picnic Baskets, trivial at 76.<br>
<br>
So there you go..with great ease and not a huge expense you can get your tailoring to 76 and not have to worry about failing on that pesky blanket.<br>
<br>
Good Luck,<br>
